{"description":"source : http://stackoverflow.com/questions/24365440/sonar-anonymous-inner-classes-containing-only-one-method-should-become-lambdas\n\nFor this rule, when the single method is making a reference to {{this}} it should not raise an issue as it becomes not fixable (you cannot reference a lambda by itself)  \n{code}\nobservable.addObserver(new Observer() {\n\n            @Override\n            public void update(Observable o, Object arg) {\n                o.deleteObserver(this);\n            }\n        });\n{code}\n","component":"SonarJava","component_version":"2.4"}